The paper proposes iterative algorithms for compressed sensing with $\ell_0$ regularization, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also provides theoretical guarantees in terms of restricted isometry property, which is a common topic in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.SP are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.NA, and cs.CV.
